Anyhow, why the big problem now?  The midnight rule has been in effect for at least the last 2 years.....at least.  I can say 2 years, because that's how long ago I found these boards (back when it was run by someone different) and the rules were the same.  You wanna get real picky about it?  The rule benefits those in certain time zones over others....but oh well.  Midnight Eastern time is 11pm my time.  I'm either asleep, watching a movie with family, or playing EQ....not sitting at the calendar waiting for it to hit the right time.  Am I bitching when someone gets to something before me?  Nope.  Why?<br>
<br>
Well, here's a little idea....if I want it bad enough, I'll be at the computer at the appropriate time, or someone from my guild will be.  End of story.  It's not like right at midnight Vox and Naggy are reserved.  <br>
<br>
Grow up and quit with this childishness.....it's petty, and you are only making yourself look like a whiny fool.<br>
<br>
/rant off<br>
